  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Arthroscopic shoulder surgery is often associated with severe postoperative pain that is&#xD;
      often significant enough to interfere with initial recovery and rehabilitation. The pain that&#xD;
      can be difficult to manage without large dose of opioid.&#xD;
&#xD;
      The study aim to explore the effect of continuous irrigation of fluids mixed with lidocaine&#xD;
      and epinephrine for analgesic consumption and postoperative pain after shoulder arthroscopy.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
